Itâs easy to let social media get a grip on youâ¦

You pick up your phone for âjust a second,â and before you know it, youâve spent an hour scrolling, chasing one dopamine hit after another, five seconds at a time.

Those little spikes of pleasure add up, pulling you deeper until youâre not even sure why you started in the first place.

But the reality is, that kind of dopamine doesnât last.

The real, soul-satisfying stuff?

Itâs out there waiting for you, and it doesnât live on a screen.

Itâs in the weights you lift, the miles you run, the food you savor, and the nights of deep, unbroken sleep.

Itâs in the moments shared over coffee with friends, not in the notifications piling up in the corner of your phone.

So hereâs the challenge: put the phone down.

Walk away from the endless loop of content and start finding that real dopamine.

Reclaim the focus and joy that comes when you choose to live fully, right here, right now.

Youâll remember what it feels like to be alive.
